Author::::Peter Maier
DateTime::::2016-03-06T20:28:11Z
Scale forming is a christalization process, due to hard water (lime) capturing heavy metals,like iron and lead. This scaling process will protect pipes from corrosion. One of the factors impacting this scaling is the acidity (ph) of the water. If acidety is low, it will dissolve the scale and the captured metals can get in the water. This probably is what happened in Flint, when they switched their water supply to the Flint River. The Flint water issue received a lot of public attention and now questions are raised how to test properly. This, while nobody cares that our open waters are still used as urinals, because nobody seems to understand that when a test requires 30 days, its 5-day value is going to miss a lot of what one intended to measure with the test. That was the reason why the Clean Water Act (CWA), the second largest federally funded public works program, failed and wasted billions. For those interested read wp.me/p5COh2-2C



